# Custom git merge drivers — INFRA-310
#
# Drivers are registered in .git/config by scripts/setup/install-merge-drivers.sh.
# That installer is auto-run by scripts/setup/install-hooks.sh, so a fresh
# checkout / linked worktree gets them after the first hook installation.

# .chump/state.sql is a regenerated artifact of .chump/state.db — chronic
# textual conflicts after parallel `chump gap reserve` calls (observed
# 1400/2400-line diffs on PRs #972 #990 on 2026-05-03). On conflict, the
# driver runs `chump gap dump --out` to produce the canonical dump from
# the local SQLite store. INFRA-367.
.chump/state.sql merge=chump-state-sql-regen

# .github/workflows/ci.yml collects append-only step additions. The ci-yml-add-row driver
# merges concurrent additions by unioning the new steps without requiring manual resolution.
.github/workflows/ci.yml merge=ci-yml-add-row

# scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit collects append-only guard blocks. The pre-commit-add-guard
# driver merges new guards by safely combining them without manual resolution.
scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit merge=pre-commit-add-guard

# Per-file gap YAMLs (docs/gaps/*.yaml) typically don't conflict (separate files per gap).
# When they do (concurrent closes on the same gap), use gap-yaml-add-line driver to
# resolve by taking ours (the current/newer state).
docs/gaps/*.yaml merge=gap-yaml-add-line

# INFRA-949: append-only YAML registries with daily conflict pattern.
#
# Both files accept ADDITIVE contributions from many PRs simultaneously
# (new ambient event kinds in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml, new tier-2/3 env var
# names in env-vars-internal.txt). Without a merge driver, two PRs that
# each add a new entry produce textual conflicts even though the changes
# don't actually conflict semantically.
#
# git's built-in `merge=union` resolver concatenates unique lines from
# both sides automatically. No custom driver script needed — `union` is
# part of git core. Verified on synthetic two-branch additive scenario
# (2026-05-13: `git merge feat-b` after both branches appended events
# produced the expected combined file with zero conflict markers).
#
# History: this conflict pattern bit five PRs today (#1597/#1605/#1609/
# #1648/#1670) requiring manual union-merge resolution via Python regex.
# Letting git do it once-and-for-all.
docs/observability/EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml merge=union
scripts/ci/env-vars-internal.txt merge=union

# INFRA-1201: web/v2/index.html is a PWA append-only hot file. Each new PWA
# feature (PRODUCT-NNN / INFRA-1011/1013-style) adds a <script src="X.js">
# entry to the script-loading block + (optionally) a <chump-X></chump-X>
# custom-element placement before the closing </body>. Both are append-only
# zones; concurrent feature PRs hit the same blocks and produce textual
# conflicts even though the additions don't actually overlap semantically.
#
# As of 2026-05-14 hot-file audit: 3 simultaneous PRs (#1827 INFRA-1011,
# #1860 PRODUCT-090, plus others) were stuck DIRTY for hours on this file.
#
# git's built-in `merge=union` concatenates unique lines from both sides.
# Same approach already validated for EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml + env-vars-internal.txt.
# Risk mitigation: pre-commit/duplicate-script-tag guard (INFRA-1201) catches
# the rare case where two PRs add THE SAME <script src="X.js"> independently.
web/v2/index.html merge=union

# INFRA-1389: extend merge-driver coverage to remaining hot shared files.
#
# All three files below follow the same append-only pattern: concurrent PRs
# add new entries at the end (new dep in Cargo.toml, new component class in
# app.js, new route arm in src/main.rs). The generic merge-driver-append-only.sh
# driver handles all three — pure-append check + tail deduplication + append.
#
# Dedup is important for Cargo.toml: two PRs that each independently add
# `serde = "1"` would otherwise double-register the entry.

# Cargo.toml — new [[bin]] entries, new [dependencies], new [features] lines.
Cargo.toml merge=cargo-toml-append

# web/v2/app.js — new component class definitions appended before the Router,
# new VIEWS map entries, new CHUMP_CADENCES subtab entries.
web/v2/app.js merge=js-append

# src/main.rs — new route handlers / match arms / use declarations appended
# at the bottom of the file (Axum router additions pattern).
src/main.rs merge=rust-main-append
